## Writing Guidelines

### Do's

- ✓ Use present tense for descriptions
- ✓ Use past tense for methods
- ✓ Define all abbreviations
- ✓ Specify sample sizes and error bars
- ✓ Describe each panel in multi-panel figures
- ✓ Use consistent terminology with main text
- ✓ Make captions self-contained (understandable without reading main text)

### Don'ts

- ✗ Interpret results (save for main text)
- ✗ Use vague terms ("various", "several")
- ✗ Omit statistical information
- ✗ Use undefined abbreviations
- ✗ Repeat main text verbatim
- ✗ Include unnecessary details

