## Statistical Notation in Captions

### Error Bars

**Format**: "Error bars represent [type] (n = [X])"

**Examples**:
- "Error bars represent mean ± SD (n = 30)."
- "Error bars represent mean ± SEM from n = 3 independent experiments."
- "Error bars represent 95% confidence intervals."

### Significance Indicators

**Format**: "Asterisks indicate statistical significance ([levels])"

**Examples**:
- "*P < 0.05, **P < 0.01, ***P < 0.001"
- "*P < 0.05 vs. control"
- "Different letters indicate significant differences (P < 0.05)"

### Sample Sizes

**Format**: "n = [X]" or "(n = [X])"

**Examples**:
- "Data are from n = 30 samples."
- "Each group contained n = 10 animals."
- "Results are from n = 3 independent experiments."

