## Checklist

Before finalizing your captions, check:

- [ ] Title sentence clearly states what is shown
- [ ] All panels are described (for multi-panel figures)
- [ ] Sample sizes are provided (n = X)
- [ ] Error bars are defined (mean ± SD or SEM)
- [ ] Statistical significance is indicated
- [ ] All abbreviations are defined
- [ ] Voice/Tense ratios match target (Passive ~70%, Present ~70%)
- [ ] Captions are self-contained (understandable without main text)
- [ ] Terminology is consistent with main text
- [ ] No interpretation included (only description)

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. **Vague titles**: "Results of experiment."
   - Better: "Effect of temperature on enzyme activity."

2. **Missing panel descriptions**: "Figure shows results."
   - Better: "(A) Control group. (B) Treatment group."

3. **Undefined error bars**: "Error bars are shown."
   - Better: "Error bars represent mean ± SD (n = 30)."

4. **Undefined abbreviations**: "WT and KO samples."
   - Better: "Wild type (WT) and knockout (KO) samples."

5. **Including interpretation**: "This shows that treatment is effective."
   - Better: "Effect of treatment on outcome." (Interpretation goes in main text)

